Detailed Description

cvmx_srio::_wr_done_counts

This register shows the number of successful and unsuccessful NwriteRs issued through this MAC. These count only considers the last NwriteR generated by each store instruction. If any NwriteR in the series receives an ERROR Status then it is reported in SRIOMAINT()_ERB_LT_ERR_DET[IO_ERR]. If any NwriteR does not receive a response within the timeout period then it is reported in SRIOMAINT()_ERB_LT_ERR_DET[PKT_TOUT]. Only errors on the last NwriteR's are counted as BAD. This register is typically not written while outbound SRIO Memory traffic is enabled.

This register is reset by the h-clock reset.
